NORTH WEST -  Running battles between police and protesters in Mahikeng are continuing. Community members have barricaded some roads in the city. While several vehicles have also been torched. Demonstrators, who are calling for his resignation, looted shops and torched a truck. At least eight people have been arrested for public violence The suspects were arrested in Montshioa and surrounding villages respectively for public violence and malicious damage to property. They are expected to appear in the Mmabatho Magistrates’ Court soon. “The police deployments will remain in the area to ensure that normality is restored in the area,” North West police said in a media statement. eNCA